# Update npm packages

When updating or reinstalling frontend dependencies, run this workflow in order from `frontend/`:

1. **Delete** `node_modules` — `rm -rf frontend/node_modules` (keep `package.json` and `package-lock.json`)
2. **Node 24** — `source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use && node -v` (must report v24.x; run `nvm install` if needed)
3. **Install** — `npm install` and note deprecation warnings
4. **Resolve deprecations** — `npm outdated`, bump versions in `package.json`, prefer patch/minor within the same major; align `eslint-config-next` with `next` and `@types/react*` with `react`
5. **Verify** — `npm run build`

Run commands yourself. Do not commit unless asked. Do not modify `.env`.

For the full workflow, use the `update-npm` skill in `.cursor/skills/update-npm/SKILL.md`.
